---
import AnimatedLink from "@/components/AnimatedLink.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
import { AvatarComponent } from "@/components/avatar-component";
import hero from "@/assets/hero.jpg";
import logo from "@/assets/white_logo.png";
import steve from "@/assets/steve.jpeg";
import justin from "@/assets/justin.jpeg";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Why Orbiter stands out from the rest when it come to static site hosting"
>
  <main>
    <div
      class={`relative flex flex-col items-center justify-start sm:min-h-[450px] min-h-[250px] w-full text-white gap-12`}
    >
      <div
        class="w-full max-w-screen-xl flex items-center justify-between gap-2 sm:my-12 my-4 sm:mb-24 px-6"
      >
        <a href="/">
          <img class="sm:h-12 h-10" src={logo.src} alt="" />
        </a>
        <div class="flex items-center sm:gap-12 gap-4">
          <AnimatedLink className="text-md sm:text-xl" href="/"
            >Home</AnimatedLink
          >
          <AnimatedLink className="text-md sm:text-xl" href="/pricing"
            >Pricing</AnimatedLink
          >
          <AnimatedLink className="text-md sm:text-xl" href="/blog"
            >Blog</AnimatedLink
          >
        </div>
      </div>

      <img
        src={hero.src}
        alt="Hero background"
        class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover -z-10"
      />

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 items-center justify-center">
        <h1 class="text-6xl sm:text-8xl flex items-center gap-2 relative z-10">
          About
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      class="flex flex-col w-full gap-6 max-w-screen-sm min-h-[800px] mx-auto p-4 mb-12"
    >
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Let's bring back the fun of the web</h2>
        <p>
          Remember when the web used to be fun? Whether you were building a
          professional site or something stupid like your newest celebrity crush
          site, there was something freeing about being able to tweak some HTML
          then quickly get your site online.
        </p>
        <p>
          We lost much of this with increasingly complex workflows. To host a
          website today, you have to jump through hoops such as:
          <ul>
            <li>Git</li>
            <li>Github</li>
            <li>Deployment pipelines</li>
            <li>Build processes</li>
            <li>Environment errors</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
          Hosting a website should be as simple as uploading your assets. That's
          exactly why we built Orbiter. We want the web to be fun (and fast)
          again.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start gap-4">
        <AvatarComponent
          client:load
          src={steve.src}
          alt="SS"
          fallbackText="SS"
        />
        <div class="prose">
          <h3>About Steve</h3>
          <p>
            Steve is a self taught developer and has a passion for developer
            tools and documentation. He's currently the Head of Developer
            Relations at Pinata where he designed <a
              target="_blank"
              href="https://ipcm.dev">IPCM</a
            >, which happen to be the perfect recipe for Orbiter's
            infrastructure. When he's not working or hacking away with Justin,
            Steve can be found in the Tennessee hills taking photos, drinking
            specialty coffee, or just spending time with his family.
          </p>
